snippet.textDisplay:
@Cleetus McFarland

Hey Cleetus, James, Coop, Alex and all!

Just want to say that I'm super stoked to see how you guys bought up the old speedway, and are working so hard to get it up and running!

I've been living in the Philippines for more than four years, and have been missing our Sweet Land of Liberty SO much, that I want to thank you all, sincerely, for helping to make these past two years much more bearable, since I turned on to your channel.

The Cleetus Mc Farland Channel, and Fasterproms and Boosted Boiz Channels have become three of my top favorite content providers on YouTube.

Whenever I watch your stuff, I'm reminded of what a beautiful country America is, and of how much I can hardly wait to come home.

You guys are like the brothers I always wished I had. All truly great guys with awesome talents, and I feel like I learn so much when I watch your videos, and the entertainment factor is awesome, too, of course.

I know that you all have your hands plenty full with getting the Freedom Factory ready to go live, and with all of your many other projects, but I have an idea that I want to toss your way...

The leaf blower trailer is pretty cool, and all, but is it possible that you all might call on one or more of your many engineering and fabricating friends, to design a build for a dedicated truck, to carry out and maybe even elaborate on the functions of the blower trailer?

I'm having a vision of a truck that features a leaf blower function and a vacuum and mulching system built into it.

I don't know if it's an idea that would be of interest to you guys, but my mind got going on it, and I'm thinking how cool it would be to see you all pick up this idea, or some variant of it, and run with it!

Best of success to you all, and best wishes from the Philippines.
